President Joe Biden has announced his nominations for key leadership positions in the U.S. Department of Homeland Security. The nominees are John Tien for Deputy Secretary, Jen Easterly for Director of Cybersecurity & Infrastructure Security Agency, Ur Jaddou for Director of United States Citizenship and Immigration Services, Chris Magnus for Commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection, Jonathan Meyer for General Counsel, and Robert Silvers for Under Secretary for Strategy, Policy, and Plans. Each nominee has a background and experience in their respective fields, ranging from military service to law and policy.